3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new approach to generating synthetic data, which is a common technique in AI research. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper focuses on improving decision boundaries for neural networks. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper evaluates the robustness of the proposed technique against adversarial attacks.
